collections.name: BRAINROTCREATED
collections.description: In internet culture, brain rot (or brainrot) describes internet content deemed to be of low quality or value, or the supposed negative psychological and cognitive effects caused by it. The term also more broadly refers to the deleterious effects associated with excessive use of digital media in general, especially short-form entertainment and doomscrolling, which may affect mental health. The term originated within the online cultures of Generation Z and Generation Alpha and has since become mainstream.

collections.name: Christophe Luciani
collections.description:
Christophe Luciani is an award-winning composer, primarily a cellist and pianist, skilled in composition and performance.

He studied the cello at the Conservatory of Boulogne-Billancourt in Paris, graduating with distinction. In 2013, he received the “Diplôme National Supérieur Professionnel de Musique” from the University of Paris. Since then, he has been pursuing his master’s degree at the University of Music and Performing Arts in Graz.

In May 2016, Christophe was awarded the SECOND PRIZE at the Grand Prize Virtuoso Competition Salzburg and subsequently worked as a cellist with the Vienna Radio Orchestra from 2016 to 2018, enriching his musical journey.

In March 2018, he obtained his master’s degree from the University of Music and Performing Arts in Graz, Austria.

In July 2023, Christophe was honored with the GRAND PRIZE for the composition of "Little French Valse n°4" at the USA MUSIC COMPOSITION AND VIDEO PRODUCTION International Competition held by IYMC, the jury commented, stating: "Marvelous. Superbly artistic, full of life and very inventive. Such a great piece, I almost wish we lived back in the 19th century. To us, one of the signs of great composers is not repeating anything that has been already said. Liszt could get together with Chopin and compose this, but not in 2023..."

Christophe publishes new compositions daily on his YouTube channel, where each new piece can be found and purchased. Additionally, he uploads MIDI visualizer tutorials to help his audience better understand and appreciate his music.
